<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="821" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1127,927,1560]" pageId="2" pageNumber="821">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,394,927,951]" pageId="2" pageNumber="821">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
Dorsum including apical margin of elytra uniformly yellow. Underside yellow, metathorax and abdomen black. Legs yellow, apices of tibiae gradually darkened, tarsi infuscate. Aedeagus as in 
<figureCitation box="[475,537,991,1016]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[153,192,1436,1455]" captionTargetBox="[185,1086,234,1405]" captionTargetId="figure-10@4.[151,1126,227,1407]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 1–4. Aedeagus (a – dorsal view; b – lateral view; c – ventral view). 1 – Mimastra badia Kimoto, 1989; 2 – M. fortipunctata Maulik, 1936; 3 – M. maai Gressitt &amp; Kimoto, 1963; 4 – M. malvi Chen, 1942. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5324960" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5324960/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="821">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
. Spermatheca as in 
<figureCitation box="[747,811,991,1015]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="5.[113,152,992,1011]" captionTargetBox="[281,917,221,957]" captionTargetId="figure-16@5.[257,928,214,960]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs. 5–9. Spermatheca. 5 – Mimastra badia Kimoto, 1989; 6 – M. fortipunctata Maulik, 1936; 7 – M. maai Gressitt &amp; Kimoto, 1963; 8 – M. pallida Jacoby, 1896; 9 – M. polita Jacoby, 1889. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5324962" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5324962/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="821">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
. Body length according to the original description: 
<quantity box="[377,538,1023,1047]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.05" metricValueMax="6.8" metricValueMin="5.3" pageId="2" pageNumber="821" unit="mm" value="6.05" valueMax="6.8" valueMin="5.3">5.30–6.80 mm</quantity>
; body length of examined 
<typeStatus box="[831,937,1024,1048]" pageId="2" pageNumber="821">paratypes</typeStatus>
: males 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.7" metricValueMax="5.9" metricValueMin="5.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="821" unit="mm" value="5.7" valueMax="5.9" valueMin="5.5">5.50–5.90 mm</quantity>
; female 
<quantity box="[286,384,1055,1079]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.75" pageId="2" pageNumber="821" unit="mm" value="5.75">5.75 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
