<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="821" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1127,927,1560]" pageId="2" pageNumber="821">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,281,1119,1143]" pageId="2" pageNumber="821">Comments.</emphasis>
According to the original description (
<bibRefCitation author="KIMOTO S." box="[705,852,1120,1144]" pageId="2" pageNumber="821" pagination="1 - 241" refId="ref13076" refString="KIMOTO S. 1989: Chrysomelidae (Coleoptera) of Thailand, Cambodia, Laos and Vietnam. IV. Galerucinae. Esakia 27: 1 - 241." type="journal article" year="1989">KIMOTO 1989</bibRefCitation>
), the type series includes the 
<typeStatus box="[190,283,1151,1175]" pageId="2" pageNumber="821">holotype</typeStatus>
deposited in BPBM and 
<specimenCount box="[550,698,1151,1176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="821" type="generic" typeStatus="paratypes">153 paratypes</specimenCount>
deposited in BPBM and the Kitakyushu Museum of Natural History and Human History (
<collectingRegion box="[681,779,1183,1207]" country="Japan" name="Fukuoka" pageId="2" pageNumber="821">Fukuoka</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[789,854,1184,1208]" name="Japan" pageId="2" pageNumber="821">Japan</collectingCountry>
). I had the opportunity to examine 
<specimenCount box="[247,386,1215,1240]" pageId="2" pageNumber="821" type="generic" typeStatus="paratypes">six paratypes</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": MEDVEDEV" authorityYear="2002" box="[421,516,1217,1240]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Mimastra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="821" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="badia">
<emphasis box="[421,516,1217,1240]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="821">M. badia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from BPBM. Three 
<typeStatus box="[734,836,1216,1240]" pageId="2" pageNumber="821">paratypes</typeStatus>
from ‘ 
<collectingRegion box="[904,1074,1215,1239]" country="Laos" name="Viangchan" pageId="2" pageNumber="821">Vientiane prov.</collectingRegion>
, Ban Van Eue, 
<date box="[259,400,1247,1271]" pageId="2" pageNumber="821" value="1967-08-30">30.VIII.1967</date>
’ that fit the original description and are in my opinion conspecific with the 
<typeStatus box="[245,338,1279,1303]" pageId="2" pageNumber="821">holotype</typeStatus>
(not examined) refer to true 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": MEDVEDEV" authorityYear="2002" box="[648,744,1281,1304]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Mimastra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="821" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="badia">
<emphasis box="[648,744,1281,1304]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="821">M. badia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Two female 
<typeStatus box="[890,992,1280,1304]" pageId="2" pageNumber="821">paratypes</typeStatus>
with yellow abdomen (from ‘ 
<collectingRegion box="[330,503,1311,1335]" country="Laos" name="Viangchan" pageId="2" pageNumber="821">Vientiane prov.</collectingRegion>
, Gi Sion vill.’ and ‘Sedone prov., Paksong’) undoubtedly belong to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1884" box="[257,429,1345,1368]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Mimastra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="821" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="submetallica">
<emphasis box="[257,429,1345,1368]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="821">M. submetallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Another 
<typeStatus box="[534,626,1344,1368]" pageId="2" pageNumber="821">paratype</typeStatus>
(female) from ‘ 
<collectingCountry box="[792,851,1344,1368]" name="Laos" pageId="2" pageNumber="821">Laos</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[861,1026,1343,1367]" country="Laos" name="Viangchan" pageId="2" pageNumber="821">Vientiane prov.</collectingRegion>
, Ban Van Eue, 
<date box="[207,320,1375,1399]" pageId="2" pageNumber="821" value="1967-02-15">15.II.1967</date>
’ is a female of an unidentified 
<taxonomicName box="[659,851,1375,1400]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Mimastra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="821" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[659,763,1377,1400]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="821">Mimastra</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
, different from 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": MEDVEDEV" authorityYear="2002" box="[1022,1120,1377,1400]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Mimastra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="821" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="badia">
<emphasis box="[1022,1120,1377,1400]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="821">M. badia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This female has a black collar on the base of the head and black margin of the elytral apex. 
<bibRefCitation author="MEDVEDEV L. N." box="[181,370,1440,1464]" pageId="2" pageNumber="821" pagination="249 - 264" refId="ref13297" refString="MEDVEDEV L. N. 2002: Jacoby's types of Chrysomelidae (Coleoptera) from Burma in the Museo Civico di Storia Naturale &quot; Giacomo Doria &quot;, Genoa. Part 3. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale &quot; G. Doria &quot; 94: 249 - 264." type="journal article" year="2002">MEDVEDEV (2002)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": MEDVEDEV" authorityYear="2002" box="[524,619,1441,1464]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Mimastra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="821" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="badia">
<emphasis box="[524,619,1441,1464]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="821">M. badia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authority="Jacoby, 1889" authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1889" box="[678,922,1439,1464]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Mimastra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="821" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polita">
<emphasis box="[678,775,1441,1464]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="821">M. polita</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="JACOBY M." box="[781,922,1439,1464]" pageId="2" pageNumber="821" pagination="147 - 237" refId="ref12866" refString="JACOBY M. 1889: List of the phytophagous Coleoptera obtained by Signor L. Fea at Burmah and Tenasserim, with descriptions of the new species. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova 27: 147 - 237." type="journal article" year="1889">Jacoby, 1889</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. My comparison of the type material of both species revealed differences in the structure of the aedeagus (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[153,192,1436,1455]" captionTargetBox="[185,1086,234,1405]" captionTargetId="figure-10@4.[151,1126,227,1407]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 1–4. Aedeagus (a – dorsal view; b – lateral view; c – ventral view). 1 – Mimastra badia Kimoto, 1989; 2 – M. fortipunctata Maulik, 1936; 3 – M. maai Gressitt &amp; Kimoto, 1963; 4 – M. malvi Chen, 1942. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5324960" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5324960/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="821">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[177,247,1504,1528]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="8.[153,192,1571,1590]" captionTargetBox="[339,926,538,1534]" captionTargetId="figure-10@8.[249,1029,520,1540]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs. 10–13. Aedeagus (a – dorsal view; b – lateral view). 10 – Mimastra pallida Jacoby, 1896; 11 – M. polita Jacoby, 1889 (lectotype); 12 – M. polita (male from India: Meghalaya); 13 – M. submetallica Jacoby, 1884. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5324966" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5324966/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="821">11–12</figureCitation>
). Based on the material examined, 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": MEDVEDEV" authorityYear="2002" box="[616,712,1505,1528]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Mimastra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="821" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="badia">
<emphasis box="[616,712,1505,1528]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="821">M. badia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is resurrected from the synonymy with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1889" box="[151,249,1537,1560]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Mimastra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="821" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polita">
<emphasis box="[151,249,1537,1560]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="821">M. polita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
